The paper discusses similarity search, which is a fundamental problem in many areas of computer science. The use of k-nearest neighbors (kNN) algorithm suggests that the paper may belong to the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-category. The applications mentioned in the abstract, such as natural language processing, content-based search, machine learning, computer vision, databases, robotics, and recommendation systems, suggest that the paper may also belong to the cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) and cs.DB (Databases) sub-categories. The use of automata-based algorithm and temporal encodings suggests that the paper may belong to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-category. Finally, the mention of computer vision in the abstract suggests that the paper may also belong to the cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) sub-category.
